    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "AMERICAN AIRLINES\nSTINSON \"FELIAM, originally called a Stinson, Jro with a Peckard\nDiesel engire was used as a North atlantie route survey plane in\n1931 by Transonerican nirlines, e predecessor company of Anerican\nAirlines.\nLater models with Lycoming engines were used domestically for route\nsurveys and instrument instruction.\nWing Loading: 15c4d go It.\nGross Height: 3,550#\nEmpty Waight: 2310g\nUseful Losd: 1245*\nCrew: 1\nPassengers: 3\nEngine: Lycoming\nTakeoff H.P.: 245\nPower Loading: 14.54\nFuel Capacity: 50 gals.\nHigh Speed: 133 mph\nCruising Speed: 120\nmph\nStall Speed: 55 mph\nService Ceiling: 14, 500°\nCost: $6,550",
